<subSubSection id="60952185B7F47FF55FF0DFE11FD3930B" type="key">
<paragraph id="2612B0A413284AB6EEB003999EB72C98" pageNumber="5">
Key to species of the 
<taxonomicName id="AC68146C0138874F6BA444F1ED973728" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notatus">S. notatus group</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="582FF0717BE6B097203338C5265BC4ED" pageNumber="5">1 Dorsal and anal fins pointed in male; 3 + 8-10 gill-rakers on first branchial arch; never bars on caudal fin in male; flank with rounded dark gray spots and without iridescent marks in female ............................................................................................................. 2</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3EC7CF79B312EB0B2F3D262F96749306" lastPageNumber="6" pageNumber="5">
- Dorsal and anal fins rounded in male; 4 + 13 gill-rakers on the first branchial arch; caudal fin with blue bars in male; flank with dark gray bars, silver bars on median portion and anterocentral black blotch with wide bluish silver to light golden contour in female ....................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="A9CBC2F42D6C30FED150AE5329E23899" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C2C14E47-3B21-4111-9EAC-E384DDD527DF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys ocellatus Costa, Nielsen &amp; de Luca 2001:25" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ocellatus">S. ocellatus</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A9401248AF1037E3420A2A6EE6B09D8A" pageNumber="6">2 Black blotch on anterocentral portion of flank in male.................................................4</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C97396F44B1E7BAD13BAFD487DE2C5C3" pageNumber="6">- No black blotch on flank in male..................................................................................3</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4190A28245441D40DE2854ED36DB3E0E" pageNumber="6">
3 Distal dark gray to black stripe on anal fin in male; bright blue spots alternating with black interspace on dorsal-fin base in male; caudal fin brownish red in male; anal-fin origin between pleural ribs of vertebrae 7 and 9 in male, and 9 and 10 in female......... ........................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="2FEB8B51A83B80F67D9C19C3BA31B788" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stellatus">S. stellatus</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B8F73D32B635DA37570F07EE80FA9E9F" pageNumber="6">
- No distal stripe on male anal fin; bright blue dots on entire dorsal fin in male; caudal fin brownish yellow in male; anal-fin origin between pleural ribs of vertebrae 9 and 10 in male, and 11 and 12 in female......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="1DFC6ADA9849112E569C3010ED8DBAB2" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:18CCA4BB-6D66-4288-8A7E-DDDCE377B762" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys rufus Costa, Nielsen &amp; de Luca 2001:29" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufus">S. rufus</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="207A3D24F1C4AF819D195C5152B12335" pageNumber="6">4 Anal fin with bright dots and no bars in male; no distal stripe on dorsal fin in male ... 6</paragraph>
<paragraph id="473E9D2E3C7FC13011EB16C96E481775" pageNumber="6">- Anal fin with oblique dark gray bars and no bright dots in male; bright blue stripe on distal edge of dorsal fin in male....................................................................................5</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DA3276401319D6764E0D4E2F1C6A85EB" pageNumber="6">
5 Caudal fin with blue dots and marginal blue stripe on dorsal half in male; blue dots over entire flank in male; tip of pectoral fin reaching between base of 5th and 7th analfin rays in male................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="A9DD8C91CE3093D19549D5EB47F25025" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notatus">S. notatus</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F795C5DD198A7D08D2A93E725D82983F" pageNumber="6">
- Caudal fin with light blue stripes parallel to fin rays, alternating with subdistal rounded light blue spots in male; tip of pectoral fin reaching between base of 1st and 3rd anal-fin rays in male................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="136900C96631E85CCD14C2F5C5FFA4F5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EF5088C8-DD0A-40DC-BE9A-1D7EE399B7A8" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys radiosus Costa &amp; Brasil 2004:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="radiosus">S. radiosus</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="84BED8245E8746B9092C49702D742946" pageNumber="6">6 Anterior portion of flank bright golden in male; humeral dark brown blotch in male ... ...................................................................................................................................... 7</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D29DEEF5C1482E0C0D4FB1FC9B78FCAD" pageNumber="6">
- Anterior portion of flank dark metallic yellow ochre in male; no humeral marks.......... ........................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="40BAA2624885D29BFCDFF286A1FE90E9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2D6458F5-F74B-44D9-AEAE-99DBA1177C83" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys similis Costa &amp; Hellner 1999:90" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="similis">S. similis</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="162A3E688192DC86BFADBBCA279FB264" pageNumber="6">
7 Five pelvic-fin rays; three purplish brown stripes on posterior portion of flank in male; no dark brown blotch on anteroventral portion of flank in male................ 
<taxonomicName id="42CF1268BAE6C6462AA3A4B09252601F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trilineatus">S. trilineatus</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="787E02876CF13152DE9B18F5579CC83E" pageNumber="6">
- Six pelvic-fin rays; purplish brown bars on posterior portion of flank in male; dark brown blotch on anteroventral portion of flank in male.................................. 
<taxonomicName id="0CC972E2C2E4DDD0D27388273738B624" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F7F23E1E-43B7-4C5B-8867-BDFBF5675CD4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys auratus Costa &amp; Nielsen 2000:8" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auratus">S. auratus</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3892A99B28713258BD4A91FBA526FF21" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8A4104B1017980CFD5F82CF3283FBAB8" pageNumber="6">Discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9FB5A0B4F0B675559CBA0459B22D5373" lastPageNumber="7" pageNumber="6">
Monophyly of the 
<taxonomicName id="7CE94D46524D5C48A40C8A8E35E4BD55" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notatus">S. notatus species group</taxonomicName>
is supported by a single synapomorphy, the A- pattern frontal squamation (Costa, 2003). This pattern differs markedly from the pattern of other congeners by the median A-frontal scale having all margins free, while in other species the whole scale margin is free in the paired E-frontal scale. The A-pattern never occurs in genera closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="144EEC7ACF652C598DC07CAB01855ED2" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BD08FA7B-788B-4285-9548-0F120F97465D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys Carvalho 1959:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Simpsonichthys</taxonomicName>
such as 
<taxonomicName id="D5D699FC2F9D81B4B143D47AA0BB796A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4ECB6721-F186-470F-BF8F-5495ADE351AB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Cynolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cynolebias Steindachner 1876:172" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cynolebias Steindachner</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="59B13711CD8DF741201665BF4C8D1ECD" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:88823811-072D-4E95-AB68-11E30A796DE0" authority="Costa, 1998" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="1998" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Megalebias" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Megalebias Costa 1998:76" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Megalebias Costa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7BC8387053258AF2FD7DA3D92D9CFF97" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AA9F26E7-8843-4CAD-8100-4C06857E5AA4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrolebias Costa 1998:75" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrolebias Costa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7CDFD2E8A312FA2E5E614CB2F5DFA0A1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E7188589-1C4C-45CC-B6E9-F46B1BE6BCEB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Cynopoecilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cynopoecilus Regan 1912:642" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cynopoecilus Regan</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FE77E3DF140B43452668F60A96CAC3E3" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:861CC503-1469-43AA-AB09-4203A97B151C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Campellolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Campellolebias Vaz-Ferreira &amp; Sierra de Soriano 1974:14" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Campellolebias Vaz-Ferreira &amp; Sierra</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="EE58329D6318B902973CBA0C18F211EF" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CE400DE5-780B-498C-81D5-B7A4D36C7B18" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Leptolebias Cynolebias Myers 1952:140" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Leptolebias Myers</taxonomicName>
(Costa, 1998, 2001, 2002), thus considered an unambiguous synapomorphy of the 
<taxonomicName id="B6DBE77B01CA554B870D8042DA1E50FB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notatus">S. notatus species group</taxonomicName>
(Costa, 2003). However, relationships among species of the 
<taxonomicName id="48DE55D1A56937D873419FD6B6CCB67D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notatus">S. notatus group</taxonomicName>
are still not clear at the present, with some potentially informative characters having great variability in outgroups. An exception is the distal blue stripe on the dorsal fin in males uniquely shared by 
<taxonomicName id="D47575C93C187DFBE45BD827E4312066" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notatus">S. notatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4546AB01ACE4E07FD815DCB87FA542E6" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EF5088C8-DD0A-40DC-BE9A-1D7EE399B7A8" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys radiosus Costa &amp; Brasil 2004:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="radiosus">S. radiosus</taxonomicName>
, the only two species of the 
<taxonomicName id="D79EB4FA07D5C49B26B0F168188717C6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notatus">S. notatus group</taxonomicName>
endemic to the upper Rio Tocantins basin, suggesting a sister group relationship between these two taxa. However, since a phylogenetic analysis is beyond the scope the present study, variability of all character states necessary to erect hypotheses of relationships of 
<taxonomicName id="5B3CE6670AE4ACF51871540FB9961C5C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EF5088C8-DD0A-40DC-BE9A-1D7EE399B7A8" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys radiosus Costa &amp; Brasil 2004:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="radiosus">S. radiosus</taxonomicName>
with other congeners is not discussed here.
</paragraph>
